  "plainText": "Brightshade Husk\nObject Info\n20\nSource\nDropped by\nMiscellaneous\n\"lunarplant_husk\"\nExclusive to:\nThis content is available only after activating the Lunar Rift\n“It's incredibly tough. I could use this!”\n–Wilson\n“Can I burn it now?”\n–Willow\n“Ah. Is not haunted anymore.”\n–Wolfgang\n“It can't hurt anyone anymore.”\n–Wendy\n“IT WAS OF NO USE TO ME ALIVE”\n–WX-78\n“An extremely resilient material. I should make use of it.”\n–Wickerbottom\n“That could be good for somethin'.”\n–Woodie\n“The blasted thing is finally dead.”\n–Maxwell\n“It hath a formidible hide, for a non-meat.”\n–Wigfrid\n“That was one mean plant. We're glad it's gone!”\n–Webber\n“Ah, raw ingredients!”\n–Warly\n“Sorry”\n–Wormwood\n“That's tough stuff!”\n–Winona\n“Unoccupied.”\n–Wortox\n“Hee-hee, it dead!”\n–Wurt\n“If you kill a ghost plant, do you get... a double ghost?”\n–Walter\n“What an interesting material, I should make use of it.”\n–Wanda\nThe Brightshade Husk is a resource exclusive to Don't Starve Together, introduced in From Beyond. It can only be obtained by killing Deadly Brightshades.\nBrightshade Husks can be used alongside Pure Brilliance to craft tools, armor, and weaponry at a Brightsmithy.\nUsage[edit | edit source]\n×4\n×4\n×2\n×4\n×4\n×4\n×6\n×6\n×3\n×3\n×4\n×2\n×2\n×3\n×3\n×3\n×20\nTrivia[edit | edit source]\nBrightshade Husks were introduced in the Taking Root update.\nView or edit this template\nResources\nAttention: The following categories are only for the players look up the page based on their first impression, they have nothing to do with the actual categories/behavior/function/tags of these items\nPlants\nNatural non-living materials\nMobs Parts\nSkins\nFeathers\nBones and horns\nGems\nShadow Resources\nLunar Resources\nCraftable Resources\nNon-natural materials\nTrinkets\nLost Relics\nTransmission Items",
